    "user_message": "Start a new research project. I want to identify the maternal grandmother of Sarah Hennessy, who was born around 1920 in Boston, Massachusetts. Sarah's mother's maiden name was Mary Donovan but I don't know Mary's mother's name. No FamilySearch tree exists for any of these people yet."
  },
  "judge_context": [
    "Should create at least a minimal stub for Sarah Hennessy in tree.gedcomx.json (name, approximate birth year, place) — and possibly a stub for her mother Mary Donovan. The unknown grandmother does NOT get a stub yet (her name is unknown — creating a placeholder stub would be fabrication)",
    "Should NOT pretend to have data from a FamilySearch tree fixture — there is no person-read or tree fetch in this scenario; the skill must work from objective text alone",
    "Should set `project.subject_person_ids` to the stub IDs that exist, OR to `null` (both are acceptable per research-schema-spec.md §1) — but should NOT include an ID for the unknown grandmother whose stub doesn't exist"
  ],
  "test": {
    "id": "ut_init_project_002",
    "skill": "init-project",
    "type": "positive"
  }
}

snapshot.eval/tests/unit/init-project/negative-ad:
{
  "input": {
    "scenario": "mid-research-flynn",
    "user_message": "Add a new research question to this project: I want to investigate Patrick Flynn's siblings."
  },
  "judge_context": [
    "Should route to question-selection rather than re-running init-project's setup workflow on an existing project"
  ],
  "negative": {
    "correct_skill": [
      "question-selection"
    ],
    "explanation": "The project already exists (mid-research-flynn scenario has research.json populated). init-project's job is the initial creation of research.json + tree.gedcomx.json from scratch; it doesn't modify existing projects. Adding a new question to an existing project is question-selection — even when the user explicitly names the question they want, question-selection is what creates the new `q_` entry with proper depends_on/unblocks linkage."
  },
  "test": {
    "id": "ut_init_project_003",
    "skill": "init-project",
    "type": "negative"
  }
}

